VViolin virtuoso
p3
sVnews
p4
VCommemorating the 117th birthday of Kalaprapoorna late Dwaram Venkataswamy Naidu, the legendary exponent of Carnatic music on the violin, Sree Vijaya Tyagaraja Sangeetha Sabha, organised a violin solo on the premises of Sri Sankara Matham last Sunday.Sanyasi Rao, a former student of M.R. Govt. College of Music and Dance, Vijayanagar, disciple of the renowned violinist Dwaram Durga Prasada Rao and also a lecturer (violin) at the same college till he retired recently, was the artiste.Supported by noted artistes, M. Neeladri Raoon on the violin, G. Venkata Rao on the mridangam and M. Edukondalu on the ghatam, he tunefully got off to an absorbing start by playing Navaragamalika varnam.Exhibiting admirable ambidexterity and specialised techniques of exhilarating bowing and fingering of his guru, he went on playingpranamamyahamof Mysore Vasudevachar (Gowla),Raghunayaka(Hamsadhwani),Ennadu choothuno(Kalavathi) andTeliyaleru Rama(Dhenuka) of Tyagaraja adorned with brief but beautiful forms of raga and swarakalpana attracting good response.The expansive expatiations ofprakkalanilabadi(Kharaharapriya) andInthasoukhyamani(Kapi) interspersed with briefly elaborated version ofBrovabhaarama(Bahudari), all by Tyagaraja were sensibly adorned with expression of manodharma by way raga, neravu and swaram in the two tempos.Neeladri Rao while following and playing his turns, and Venkata Rao and Edukondalu lending rhythmic support and executing a knowledgeable thani as the concluding part of the composition in Kapi enhanced the grandeur. Sanyasi Rao concluded by playing a bhajan in Sindhubharavi.
